# Covex on-box monitor (covex-watch) configuration.
#
# Install location on the box: /opt/covex-monitor/alert.env   (chmod 600)
# This file is read both by the systemd unit (EnvironmentFile) and sourced
# directly by covex-watch.sh, so plain KEY=value lines work.
#
# ARMING THE ALERTS
# -----------------
# Set COVEX_ALERT_WEBHOOK to a Slack OR Discord incoming-webhook URL. The monitor
# POSTs a JSON body carrying BOTH a "text" key (Slack renders this) and a
# "content" key (Discord renders this), so either platform's generic webhook
# displays the alert without any per-platform formatting.
#
#   - Slack:   https://hooks.slack.com/services/T000/B000/XXXXXXXX
#   - Discord: https://discord.com/api/webhooks/000000/XXXXXXXX
#   - ntfy:    https://ntfy.sh/<your-topic>   (also renders the text body)
#
# When this is UNSET or empty, the monitor treats the box as healthy and logs
# "ALERT WEBHOOK UNARMED; would have sent: ..." to the journal instead of paging.
# This is intentional: an unarmed box is ready, not broken.
#
COVEX_ALERT_WEBHOOK=

# Independent tip-staleness window, in seconds. The monitor persists the node's
# tip_daa and the time it first saw it; if the tip has not advanced within this
# window it goes RED with reason node_tip_frozen. This is independent of the
# backend's in-process 600s watchdog (which resets on a backend restart), so it
# still catches a freeze that spans a restart. Default 900 (15 minutes).
#
COVEX_TIP_STALE_SECONDS=900

# ---- Optional overrides (sane defaults baked into covex-watch.sh) ------------
# COVEX_TIP_NETWORK=testnet-12          # which node_sync network to hold the tip for
# COVEX_DISK_RED=85                     # disk percent used -> RED
# COVEX_DISK_WARN=80                    # disk percent used -> WARN
# COVEX_DISK_MOUNTS="/ /mnt/covex-data" # mount points to check
# COVEX_TLS_RED_DAYS=14                 # cert days remaining -> RED
# COVEX_TLS_HOSTS="hightable.pro oracle.hightable.pro"
# COVEX_UNITS="covex-backend.service koracle.service kaspad-tn12.service nginx.service"
